# CueCode agent development

When editing files matched by this rule, read the relevant **agent skill** under
`.cursor/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` before implementing. Do not duplicate skill
bodies in responses — follow them.

## Skill router

| Task | Skill | References |
|------|-------|------------|
| Tone, brainstorm vs fix, pacing | `engineering-partner` | `references/mode-detection.md` |
| AI product doctrine, moat vs parity, surface map | `cuecode-ai-maxxing` | `references/ai-surface-map.md`, `references/cursor-parity-vs-moat.md` |
| Product scope, user journeys, spec alignment | `product-builder` | `references/product-thinking-checklist.md` |
| GPUI panels, modals, agent UI, icons, UX | `ui-ux-gpui` | `references/ui-surfaces.md`, `references/ux-review-checklist.md` |
| Prompts, models, context, tools, streaming, ACP | `agent-inference` | `references/inference-flow.md`, `references/prompt-editing-guide.md` |
| Rust implementation quality | `rust-quality` | `references/pre-submit-checklist.md` |
| GPUI test failures | `gpui-test` | skill body |
| Product specs, rebrand, roadmap | — | `.cursor/rules/cuecode-specs.mdc`, `.cursor/specs/` |

## Quick routing

- **New AI/agent feature** → `cuecode-ai-maxxing` + `product-builder`, then `ui-ux-gpui` and/or `agent-inference`.
- **New user-facing feature** → `product-builder` first, then `ui-ux-gpui` and/or `agent-inference`.
- **UI-only change** → `ui-ux-gpui` + `rust-quality`.
- **Prompt/tool/model change** → `agent-inference` + `rust-quality`; check UI if user-visible.
- **Both UI and inference** → all three hub skills, smallest diff that satisfies the user path.

## Principles

- User path before crate names; happy and unhappy paths.
- Match existing patterns in `agent_ui` / `agent` — do not invent parallel UX.
- `./script/clippy` and targeted tests before calling work done (`rust-quality`).
- Link PRs to `.cursor/specs/` sections when implementing CueCode product work.

Communication voice and modes: `.cursor/rules/cuecode-comms.mdc` → `engineering-partner` skill.
